org.opendaylight.controller.networkconfig.neutron

Interface INeutronFirewallRuleAware


  • public interface INeutronFirewallRuleAware
    This interface defines the methods a service that wishes to be aware of Firewall Rules needs to implement

    • Method Detail

      • canCreateNeutronFirewallRule

        int canCreateNeutronFirewallRule(NeutronFirewallRule firewallRule)
        Services provide this interface method to indicate if the specified firewallRule can be created
        Parameters:
        firewallRule - instance of proposed new Firewall Rule object
        Returns:
        integer the return value is understood to be a HTTP status code. A return value outside of 200 through 299 results in the create operation being interrupted and the returned status value reflected in the HTTP response.

      • neutronFirewallRuleCreated

        void neutronFirewallRuleCreated(NeutronFirewallRule firewallRule)
        Services provide this interface method for taking action after a firewallRule has been created
        Parameters:
        firewallRule - instance of new Firewall Rule object

      • canUpdateNeutronFirewallRule

        int canUpdateNeutronFirewallRule(NeutronFirewallRule delta,
                               NeutronFirewallRule original)
        Services provide this interface method to indicate if the specified firewallRule can be changed using the specified delta
        Parameters:
        delta - updates to the firewallRule object using patch semantics
        original - instance of the Firewall Rule object to be updated
        Returns:
        integer the return value is understood to be a HTTP status code. A return value outside of 200 through 299 results in the update operation being interrupted and the returned status value reflected in the HTTP response.

      • neutronFirewallRuleUpdated

        void neutronFirewallRuleUpdated(NeutronFirewallRule firewallRule)
        Services provide this interface method for taking action after a firewallRule has been updated
        Parameters:
        firewallRule - instance of modified Firewall Rule object

        Parameters:

        Returns:
        integer the return value is understood to be a HTTP status code. A return value outside of 200 through 299 results in the delete operation being interrupted and the returned status value reflected in the HTTP response.
